answer: @divbyzero For a (very very) brief time, `env PASS=SECR cmd PASS` will show; then for the duration of cmd `cmd PASS` will show. Using export, no env phase will be there, and only `cmd PASS` will be visible. Yes you are right, export is far better. But it seems you have some control on cmd, so perhaps you can even avoid the "PASS" argument and let cmd fetch the secret from a fixed environment var, perhaps scrambled or masqueraded as innocent "CPFLAGS=terces"...
